                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The clockwork mage uses a mechanical wand as a focus to channel magical energy. This wand is built into the clockwork mage's chest, with only the crystal at the end exposed. The mage can Interact to the remove the wand, or someone else can remove it with a @Check[type:thievery|dc:25|traits:action:disable-a-device] check to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Disable a Device]. The clockwork mage becomes unable to cast any spells except cantrips while the wand is removed.</p>\n<p>When removed, the clockwork wand is a <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Magic Wand (2nd-Rank Spell)]{Magic Wand}</em> containing the last 1st-rank innate spell the clockwork mage cast (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Fear], if the clockwork Belimarius hasn't yet cast a 1st-rank spell in this adventure). The spells are placed within the wand while the mage is created, and the creator can substitute other arcane spells of the appropriate rank.</p>"
